  <section>
    <h2>Accessibility</h2>

    <h3>Inert Toggling</h3>
    <p>The hidden face is always marked <code>inert</code>. This means screen readers only announce the currently visible face, and interactive elements on the hidden face cannot receive focus.</p>

    <h3>Trigger Modes</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Whole-card trigger</strong> (no <code>data-flip</code> children): The card itself gets <code>role="button"</code>, <code>tabindex="0"</code>, and <code>aria-label="Flip card"</code>.</li>
      <li><strong>Explicit triggers</strong> (<code>data-flip</code> children): The trigger buttons are the keyboard targets. No role is added to the container.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Focus Management</h3>
    <p>When flipping, focus moves to the first interactive element on the newly visible face (buttons, links, inputs, or elements with <code>autofocus</code>).</p>

    <h3>Reduced Motion</h3>
    <p>When <code>prefers-reduced-motion: reduce</code> is active, the flip animation duration is set to <code>0s</code>. The state still toggles, but without animation.</p>
  </section>

